Steps:
1. Send POST /rgm/api/vaults with body: {"tokenVaultName":"Vault Without TSP Code","custodianIdList":["custodian009"]}
2. Verify HTTP response code
3. Verify error body structure

1. Send POST /rgm/api/vaults with body: {"tspCode":"998","tokenVaultName":"Empty Custodian Vault","custodianIdList":[]}
2. Verify HTTP response code
3. Verify response is valid JSON

1. Send POST /tvm/api/issuer with header X-TV-ID: {{vaultId}} and body: {"issuerName":"DBBL","issuerCode":"0421","encryptedTransportKey":"{{encryptedTransportKey}}","kcv":"{{kcv}}","realTimePanEnrollment":"Y"}
2. Verify HTTP response code
3. Extract and store issuerId

1. Send POST /tvm/api/bin/single with header X-TV-ID: {{vaultId}} and body: {"issuerId":"{{issuerId}}","binControllerId":"1234","binValue":"63999603","brandType":"06","ianLen":7}
2. Verify HTTP response code
3. Extract and store binId

1. Send POST /tvm/api/account-range with header X-TV-ID: {{vaultId}} and body: {"issuerId":"{{issuerId}}","binId":"{{binId}}","panLowerLimit":"1100000","panUpperLimit":"9000000","listOfExpiry":[{"quarter":"Q1","year":2027},{"quarter":"Q2","year":2027},{"quarter":"Q3","year":2027}]}
2. Verify HTTP response code
3. Extract and store accountRangeId

1. Send POST /tvm/api/token-requestor/token-use/setup with header X-TV-ID: {{vaultId}} and body: {"merchantInfos":[{"merchantId":"123456789012345","merchantName":"Merchant"}],"modeOfTransaction":"01","trId":"{{tokenRequestorId}}"}
2. Verify HTTP response code
3. Verify modeOfTransaction=01 in request

1. Send POST /tvm/api/token-life/authorization with header X-TV-ID: {{vaultId}} and body: {"requestorId":"{{tokenRequestorId}}","minPeriodInMonths":0,"maxPeriodInMonths":70,"issuerId":"{{issuerId}}"}
2. Verify HTTP response code
3. Verify minPeriodInMonths=0 and maxPeriodInMonths=70 in request

1. Send POST /api/tokens/tokenize with X-TSP-TR-ID: {{tokenRequestorId}}
2. Set mac to: AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA (tampered)
3. Verify HTTP response code

1. Send POST /api/validate-mac with body: {plainText:{{tokenizedCipherText}}, transportKey:{{requestorTransportKey}}, mac:{{tokenizedMac}}}
2. Verify HTTP response code
3. Verify response indicates MAC is valid (true / valid / success)

1. Send POST /tvm/api/tokens/de-tokenize/issuer with header X-TV-ID: {{vaultId}} and body: {mode:VERIFY, token:{{issuedToken}}, tokenExpiry:09/27, tokenRequestorId:{{tokenRequestorId}}, txData:{posEntryMode:07, merchantId:123456789012345}}
2. Verify HTTP response code
3. Extract and store detokenizationCipherText

1. Send POST /rgm/api/vaults with body: {"tspCode":"998","tokenVaultName":"Mixed BIN Vault","custodianIdList":["{{generatedCustodian1}}","{{generatedCustodian2}}"]}
2. Verify HTTP 200 or 201 and extract vaultId
3. Register proprietary BIN under vaultId: POST /tvm/api/bin/single with brandType=06, binValue={{generatedProprietaryBin}}
4. Register scheme BIN under same vaultId: POST /tvm/api/bin/single with brandType=03, binValue={{generatedSchemeBin}}
5. Verify both binIds returned and stored
6. Verify both BINs are linked to the same vaultId in GET /tvm/api/bin or equivalent listing endpoint

1. Send POST /tvm/api/tokens/de-tokenize/issuer with header X-TV-ID={{vaultId}}, body: {mode:VERIFY, token:{{T_EXPIRED}}, tokenExpiry:01/23 (past date), tokenRequestorId:{{tokenRequestorId}}, txData:{posEntryMode:07, merchantId:123456789012345}}
2. Verify HTTP response code
3. Verify error body indicates token is expired or inactive

1. Re-prepare tokenization with same pan={{generatedPan}}, same deviceId, but now deviceInfo: {nfcCapable:true, nfcEnabled:true, walletId:{{walletId}}, seId:{{seId}}, fingerPrint:{{fingerPrint}}}
2. Send POST /api/tokens/tokenize with X-TSP-TR-ID={{tokenRequestorId}}
3. Verify HTTP 200
4. Verify token issued and tokenizedCipherText stored

1. Attempt detokenization of T1: POST /tvm/api/tokens/de-tokenize/issuer with header X-TV-ID={{vaultId}}, body: {mode:VERIFY, token:{{T1}}, tokenExpiry:09/27, tokenRequestorId:{{tokenRequestorId}}, txData:{posEntryMode:07, merchantId:123456789012345}}
2. Verify HTTP response code
3. Confirm whether the system checks current device NFC state at detokenize time or only at issuance time

1. Prepare tokenization for PROPRIETARY card: POST /api/mocker/encrypt/card-holder-data with pan={{proprietaryPan}}, deviceInfo: {nfcCapable:true, nfcEnabled:true, walletId:{{multiSchemeWalletId}}, deviceId:{{deviceId}}, seId:{{seId}}, fingerPrint:{{fingerPrint}}}
2. Send POST /api/tokens/tokenize with X-TSP-TR-ID={{tokenRequestorId}}
3. Verify HTTP 200, extract and decrypt token — confirm token range is from proprietaryBin token range
4. Prepare tokenization for SCHEME card (e.g. Mastercard): pan={{mastercardPan}}
5. Repeat tokenize call — verify token drawn from Mastercard token range
6. Prepare tokenization for second SCHEME card (e.g. Visa): pan={{visaPan}}
7. Repeat tokenize call — verify token drawn from Visa token range
